query:
I have a GraphQL schema and I want to make sure users can only access their own orders, not other users' orders. How should I enforce field-level authorization? Should I use a directive like @auth or handle this in resolvers? Here's the schema:

type Query {
  orders(userId: ID!): [Order!]!
}

type Order {
  id: ID!
  userId: ID!
  total: Float!
}
